cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.DB. 

This paper deals with algorithms for preprocessing data structures (lists and trees) to efficiently answer range mode and range median queries. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and algorithmic techniques (cs.AL). The paper also involves computational geometry (cs.CG) as it deals with paths in trees. Additionally, the paper involves data mining (cs.DM) as it deals with finding modes and medians in sequences of labels. Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of databases (cs.DB) as it involves preprocessing data structures for efficient querying.
